  Asymmetric Clipping                                                                                     
  - AC/DC — "Back in Black" (Marshall amps biased hot — the push-pull power tubes clip asymmetrically,
  adding 2nd harmonic warmth)                                                                             
  - The Kinks — "You Really Got Me" (Dave Davies slashed his speaker cone, creating uneven physical
  distortion — one of the first deliberate asymmetric tones on record)                                    
  - Blues Breaker / Marshall Bluesbreaker pedal tones: one diode clips the positive half harder than the  
  negative — that "transparent overdrive" character is even harmonics
